\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 That's where you used to play was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Yes. Yes, you was out of bounds down there but you went. Oh - every tiddler there was - every type of tiddler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Did you ever go swimming in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Yes, we were all taught to swim in the horse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6160996\charrsid13067595 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 pond there. And of course if - the park keeper or even the policeman saw you - you know, a - a boy can be very elusive, he's gone. And so - how that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 What other kind of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Everything. In the road - there's the old fashioned bumps, and while you're on - ju
mping over - what is like that - one called cut lump, there was lamp release, there was warning echo.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 What are all these things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 I'll explain this one to you, tin can copper. You know in the roadside there's water valves. That would be a base. A
nd this base was right opposite Beckets place, the court}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6160996\charrsid13067595 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
way, I'll tell you about that - led onto the Dryings. Well - one boy would have to retri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6160996\charrsid13067595 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
ved a tin can that thrown down towards Townsend Road. And on his way back he would come back backwards, arrive
 at the base, and he should put the base of the tin on that base, then he'd look round and - if he would see any of them hiding. If he could see somebody hiding he could recognise, he'd bang the tin down on the base, one, two, three, Wally - Wally Leanard
 
in number 28. But if he couldn't find anybody, he'd have to - go out and seek. And if you could dodge him to get back to that base and say, one, two, three, I'm home. And that was the game. But anybody caught out he was - in turn would have to retrieve th
e can as it was thrown down the street And they call that tin can copper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 What was Cut Lump?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
Cut Lump. Yes. It's - on the - idea of bumps. One man would go down - the team would jump over him, and the last one to land, say you landed there, from that chalk mark of where you - where you start you'd go to the next. And that'd be a o}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6160996\charrsid13067595 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
ner, and he's got to jump from that point there, not come over, it's on the same part - line as - in - as in tennis, football you see. From that - and jump over - over y
ou. And if everybody succeeded the last man would go on, there'd be a tower. See. Cut lump. The one to fail will have to go down and take the stand. And the lamp release - was a game which was between two sections of lamp posts. So on one side of the road
'
d be up there and the other one down here. Be two teams. One - would be in - in the interior of that section there, and the - you'd encourage the others to run right the way through without being caught or touched. But - if one of your team was caught the
n one of those protecting the area would have to go on the kerb line. And you - you outside would encourage him, come near him, and if you could push him off that kerb line you'd release your man from the base. Lamp release. That's how it went on.
