\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 No, no, because your - your aim wouldn't be to - it wasn't - it would be to go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6160996\charrsid13067595  through it and not to - wilfully}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595  disturb the sheep, 'course the sheep would }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7303732\charrsid13067595 shier}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595  at you naturally as you approach. But - Regents Park every summer was full of sheep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Who was it you played with, just people who were at school with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Yes. It would be your friends about your - your own household, and - as you got older and m
ore - organized you'd play - the top of the street, or - another turning. And then the school days naturally the more you made friends, you'd -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Did the boys come from the same area as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Yes. In - all the same area went to the same school. Yes
. See so you - you knew - you - you knew about each others characters. Because, as I say, you - you - you jumped school - on your age group, not on ability, on age group. So your friends were always there all the time.
