 held a meeting at Buckkingham Palace, to think that I so many years beforehand was in the same group, but our Scouts Hall was in Charlotte Street. An old ramshackle of a place. Which it was a bungalow type of building - there was an upstairs but it was a
l
l sort of a semi loft where we kept all the camping equipment, pots and pans. It was a good job because - otherwise the rain would have poured down into the hall itself. 'Cos when it rained every pot was put there for - use - catching all the drips and ev
erything else that came through. That was the First Marylebone - Scouts.
