d this as well as class matches of the house matches, there'd be school matchers, inter-school like - Byehill Road would play - Bell Street, or Gateforth Street, or High Street Marylebone, which was a - a High School in those days, and they were boys of s
i
xteen, and we were thirteen. They left there at sixteen. But we would play them. In fact we took the shield away from then in 1921. But any rate - then the other interests of life of course - everybody went to Sunday school. Everybody went to church Sunda
y.
