\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Yes. We had a little box, I remember coming home from school - and I heard something playing in the kitchen, and mother 
was playing this gramaphone and know what the tune was? Destiny Waltz. Yes. Destiny Waltz, yes, I can recall that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 So sport and music was your forte really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Yes, I was keen, I was keen from - even schooldays like singing - in the school choir, i
n - classes you know as part of your subjects, sing. Like tunes as you know by - I mentioned Barbara Allen and - Drink to me only and all that. I was always keen to sing, I loved singing. And - and of course when ragtime came in that was - oh that was mar
vellous, lovely, you see I was a new generation. I was going into the twenties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Did you ever go to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7303732\charrsid13067595  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 any concerts or music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 As regards to music - music halls as you say, the Old Met - Edgware Road, the Kilburn Empire. The Bedford, Camden Town
. I can remember as a teenager just finding me feet - I'd have a friend come round to me about - half past eight, twenty to nine, Ed, let's go to the Bedford, the last house. As you know there were two houses then. Six o'clock. Nine o'clock. Right. From t
hat point there - penny fared take us to the Britannia and of course just round the corner would be the Bedford. And those were the days of vaudeville and - Harry Tate, the motor car - Gertie Getano - Nellie Wallace.
