\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 After, yes, yes, after, early twenties. Early twenties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Did your mother and father ever go to the music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Yes, Kilburn Empire, I'd sometimes go with - with mother to Kilburn Empire. It was easier for us to get there than go all t
he way down to the Metropolitan. But as I got older, especially in the thirties,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7303732\charrsid13067595  late twenties and thirties, I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
 would visit either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 How about before the first world war, would they go on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Yes, they had - they - I think they did because 
- although mum didn't - mum or dad didn't talk a lot about it, I think - their - their days were spent in courtship more. Didn't get about so much. The working day was a heavy day for them. In - in their teenage days, and - their courting days were of cou
rse, local Primrose Hill was -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Did they have any particular friends of their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
No, no, the - no, it was more family, 'cos as you know so many brothers and sisters, no. No, there wasn't a lot of friends of the family. You - you accepted the fa
ct that you knew of everybody but you didn't - you didn't have to, it was that end of it then. And of course - life goes so that you - you can't have too many keep crowding into the same house otherwise the house is - not your own. You've got to keep priv
acy to an extent. Yet you knew if there was a row going on next door, there's a row going up Beckets Place, you were just part of it, you enjoyed it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 So the only people who would really come round would be your relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Relatives, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 And you'd go around to see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
Yes. That's how you would exchange. Yes. Yes, after all you had no other means of entertainment, you had no - see you've got to forget radio, television and all that, forget all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Would your mother and father play any games with you in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
Yes. Not - yes, card games. Sevens, the old fashioned game of Sevens. And of course - in the summer, Regents Park attracted you because the band would play every - Sunday. Relations would meet out there. And of
 course - games was taboo, you couldn't play games, no - the Sabbath was entirely the Sabbath. Any - anything from serious music was frowned on. In fact jumped on. A ball, you couldn't produce a ball not - we would - compensate ourselves by - stuffing an 
ordinary handkerchief with grass, and - and sort of making a - improvised ball to throw at each other. And further tall - fur - further too that, as you got older it was a one way of boy meeting girl, round the bandstand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 That was on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Sunday, yes. That was Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 What kind of bandstand would it be, Salvation Army type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 No, no, military bands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 That would be all right to play that kind of music would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Yes, it would be - all the old - like as - as near as you might 
get - a - a - apart from classics you might get a bit of light opera. Those were two - pioneers of - say the Chocolate Soldiers and all that sort of music, bit light, and - later, Rose Marie you might hear.
