\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 No. That was - that wasn't only frowned on but you were jumped on, two swearing. No swearing. In fact - the words }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7303732\charrsid13067595 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595  ain}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7303732\charrsid13067595 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 t or she you were jumped on. Don't refer to her as she, don't say her. Refer to the person at - by its name. Mrs or Mr, never she or what. No. You'd be jumped on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
When you were living in St Johns Wood can you remember whether there was anyone that you used to say that she's a real lady or that's a real gentleman or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Yes. Well anybody that come out of the by turnings - you'd refer to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 What did the people do in these big houses, what kind of jobs did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Well - if there was any work at all they would be somebody in the City. They would entertain, especially when - the 
session came round of Oxford and Cambridge and Eton and Harrow which took a week in July. Cricket matches at Lords. The local people would be of that class and set, and there'd be morning dress, all go to Lords, and as it extended a week, they would proba
bly entertain their guests - at their own house. Because in the vast gar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7303732\charrsid13067595 dens I've known - tents and mar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
quees being erected there and dance bands play in them. Which we'd sit on the kerb on the opposite side of the road and listen to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Who would be the most important people in the area, would it be these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
Yes. Recognise - the - the rich people. They were recognised as being the important people as - oh that's a lady, or that's a sir, that's the respect you had, you were brought up to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Did anyone ever call your mother or father sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
Oh no. No, no, no, No. The best - probably could refer - some would refer as - oh this is my daily help. Some of the nicer - persons of that class were referred to as a - as Mrs Turner. But major
ity was inclined to look down. Look down, yes, very much. Very much. It was accepted because after all that was the mode of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 What were the different groups in those days, say these people, what other kind of groups would there be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Well as far as views like political views you mean?
