\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 No, not so much that as different social groups, the people who lived in these big houses, and you say yourself sort of working class?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Yes, well they're entirely on their own. They lived in the clean o
f the respectability and actually - as I say that - if you were seen walking along these turnings they'd would want to - the police would want to know, what are you doing up here? See, so that would meet your question there half way wouldn't it? And - whe
n
 they - when they caught a local tradesman, of course the red carpet was laid out for them, yes madam. In fact you wouldn't refer to her as a - as Mrs Richardson say, yes madam, yes sir. I think you - you'd be asking, you'd be speaking out of turn - be sl
ightly on the rude side to refer to as say Mrs - Mrs Jenkins or Mrs Is}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7303732\charrsid13067595 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 ael, madam or sir,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Were you brought up to touch your hat to these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Yes. Always be most respectful. Most respectful. In fact - cap in hand. Take off your cap. And hold i
n hand to talk - if you were asked to talk. Yes sir, yes madam. And of course very much in evidence too - the classification of the tradesman calling at the tradesman's entrance. Was only two persons - two trades allowed to go to the front door, that was 
the postman and the paper boy. Because as you know, you - you use that front letterbox, otherwise, you'd be a - a rude - intrusion, a breach of protocol to use the front porch. Tradesman's entrance, you'd be - if you did you'd be readily told. And -

