\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 
Well no you - no, in - in the working class, there - there's hardly a - there isn't - naturally the shop keeper would feel more important. It's like the suburban - over 
the - over the - over the working class of a town. There would be a slight there - for instance - there was a butcher named Chapman. The '14 war made his fortunes better than they were. And at that period of time - mother - would go to the mothers meeting
 
with Mrs Chapman. And then after the '14 war in the twenties, Chapman moved from - Charlotte Street area - working class, and went up into the local high street, lush territory. And that's the time when I met his daughter, Connie. But they frowned on the 
fact that I was keeping company with Connie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 So it was possible to move upwards?
