\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Well with the local clergy, he was a friend of everybody}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7303732\charrsid13067595 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 s. The schoolteacher, they - they always came from afar. They were - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7303732\charrsid13067595 importe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 d into the area, but never lived in the area. No, they - for the - I would say that the school - the teacher - in my day - he was dedicated to 
improve his pupil. And - in some senses there a - a great relationship, now for instance My Mr Timms, him and - and myself were great friends. There was - there wasn't a thing I wouldn't do for him. There was great respect there. I - I had a love for my t
eacher and he had a great respect for me. That - that - that was fostered. Of course you had your dislikes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 What kind of things did he think was important, what was he like on things like punctuality or manners, tidiness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Well let me give you jus
t a little insight here. One evening I should have played for school - at cricket. We were playing Bell Street in Regents Park. But I'd - refused on the grounds that I wanted to go into Lords, there was a big county and I wanted to see some County members
.
 And when Mr Timms heard of that - before closure of school he called me in front of the class. I've got it written down there as a matter of fact. And he - he says, Turner, I understand that you've refused to play for school. I said, yes sir. You know I 
w
as quite honest. Well why, he said. I said, because the reason that I want to go into Lords, there's a - important County match there and there's men I want to see. And after a pause he says to me, you mean to say that you put your own - selfish desires -
 
in front of - school? School is expecting you to play to represent them, and you're going selfishly for your own desires? And I didn't realize the significance of that. But he'd given me a wigging after - first of all a lecture, then a wigging, and I felt
 
so hurt. Hurt in the respect that he hurt my feelings, I hadn't realized - what I had done. And also our friendship had - had sort of been strained. Well after several days of thinking about it, I knew full well that I'd been - foolishly and selfishly thi
nking of - just myself. Or rather selfishly. And that was a - one of the finest tonics I think I ever got. He pushed it home to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 Did you have the same teacher all the way through?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8675640 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 No. It did fluctuate on several occasions, but I was very fortunate, I always seemed to have my Mr Timms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4738731 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248743\charrsid13067595 What other kind of things did you like at school?
